# Receipts OCR Tool — Development Rules

## Scope

- Build and maintain **receipt image → OCR → editable table → CSV export** only.
- Do not add kakeibo reconciliation/matching UI until explicitly requested.
- Keep independent from the Parcel demo (`src/index3.js`) and `src/news/**`.
- Reuse kakeibo Google Sign-In (`src/kakeibo/auth.js`) for access gating; do not
  upload receipt tables to Google as part of login.

## Privacy (critical)

- Receipt images are sent to **Google Cloud Vision** for OCR — this is intentional
  and must stay clearly disclosed in the UI and docs.
- **Never commit** real receipt images, OCR dumps, or exported receipt CSVs.
- The Vision API key must **never** be hardcoded or committed. Users enter it in
  the UI; store only in `localStorage` (`receipts:visionApiKey:v1`).
- Do not log API keys or full OCR text in production UI paths; status messages
  should use file counts / error codes.

## Free-tier guardrails

- Default monthly cap is `FREE_TIER_MONTHLY_LIMIT` (1000) in `config.js`.
- Always check `planBatch` / remaining quota **before** calling Vision.
- Increment usage only after a successful Vision response.
- Document that users should also set a GCP quota ceiling.

## Data model

- Core parsing/CSV helpers (`parseReceiptText.js`, `receiptCsv.js`, `quota.js`,
  `config.js`, `errors.js`) must stay framework-agnostic plain JS (no DOM) so
  unit tests can run under `node --test`.
- v1 granularity is **one CSV row per line item** (not one row per receipt).
- `receiptId` groups lines from the same image; preserve it on export.
- CSV columns live in `RECEIPT_CSV_HEADER` — keep export and docs in sync.

## Testing

- Add/keep unit tests in `test/receipts/` for parsers, CSV, and quota math.
- Use fabricated OCR text only — never real merchant receipts as fixtures.

## UI

- Separate Parcel entry: `receipts.html` → `src/receipts/receiptsApp.js`.
- Dependency-free browser UI (no frameworks), same visual language as kakeibo.
